    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We may need \"autofocus: true/false/auto\" Because otherwise people setting \"true\" would think that there will be always autofocus. While auto would be the \"smart\" one from the description that should fit most use cases?\n\nautofocus: true => always autofocus (query or no query set)\nautofocus: false => always disabled\nautofocus: auto => (default) smart autofocus\n\n@bobylito Not sure to answer your question here, let me know\n",
    "created_at": "2015-09-30T09:10:40Z",
